@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "The Pledge";
}

<section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>The Pledge</h1>
        <p class="lead">Three tiers of certification &mdash; because honesty requires nuance.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="text-center mb-5" style="max-width:750px;margin:0 auto;">
            <h2>Understanding the Tiers</h2>
            <hr class="section-divider" />
            <p class="text-warm-gray">
                The world isn&rsquo;t black and white, and neither is the relationship between humans and AI.
                Our tier system provides an honest, transparent way for creators and businesses to communicate
                exactly how their work was made.
            </p>
            <p class="text-warm-gray" style="font-size:0.9rem;font-style:italic;">
                In the spirit of full disclosure: this website would currently qualify as Craft Assisted.
                We&rsquo;re working on that.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="card card-cp tier-card tier-assisted">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="tier-icon">🥉</div>
                        <h3 class="card-title">Craft Assisted</h3>
                        <p class="text-warm-gray">
                            AI may have been used as a supporting tool, but a human led, shaped, and took
                            responsibility for the final output.
                        </p>
                        <hr />
                        <h5>What this means:</h5>
                        <ul class="text-warm-gray">
                            <li>AI tools were used during the creative or production process</li>
                            <li>A human was in control of all significant decisions</li>
                            <li>The final output was reviewed, refined, and approved by a person</li>
                            <li>The creator takes full responsibility for the work</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="small text-warm-gray fst-italic">
                            <strong>Examples:</strong> A writer who uses AI for research and first-draft suggestions but
                            writes the final piece. A developer who uses AI-assisted coding tools but architects and
                            reviews all code.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="card card-cp tier-card tier-verified">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="tier-icon">🥈</div>
                        <h3 class="card-title">Craft Verified</h3>
                        <p class="text-warm-gray">
                            No AI was used in creating the final product or service. Conceived, created, and
                            delivered by human hands and minds.
                        </p>
                        <hr />
                        <h5>What this means:</h5>
                        <ul class="text-warm-gray">
                            <li>No generative AI was used in the creation of the product or service</li>
                            <li>Traditional digital tools (spell-check, calculators, etc.) are permitted</li>
                            <li>The entire creative process was human-driven</li>
                            <li>AI may exist elsewhere in the supply chain (e.g., logistics)</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="small text-warm-gray fst-italic">
                            <strong>Examples:</strong> A hand-written novel. A logo designed from scratch by a graphic
                            designer. Software written entirely by human engineers.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="card card-cp tier-card tier-pure">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="tier-icon">🥇</div>
                        <h3 class="card-title">Craft Pure</h3>
                        <p class="text-warm-gray">
                            No AI was used anywhere in the supply chain &mdash; from origin to delivery.
                            The highest standard of human craft.
                        </p>
                        <hr />
                        <h5>What this means:</h5>
                        <ul class="text-warm-gray">
                            <li>No generative AI at any point in the entire value chain</li>
                            <li>Raw materials, production, packaging, and delivery are all AI-free</li>
                            <li>The most rigorous standard of human-made certification</li>
                            <li>Requires full supply chain transparency</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="small text-warm-gray fst-italic">
                            <strong>Examples:</strong> Handmade artisan goods from sourced natural materials.
                            A farm-to-table restaurant with fully human operations.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4 mb-lg-0">
                <h2>Why tiers matter</h2>
                <hr class="section-divider" style="margin-left:0;" />
                <p class="text-warm-gray">
                    A binary &ldquo;AI or not&rdquo; label would be dishonest. The reality is that AI exists on a
                    spectrum, and so does its use. A photographer who uses AI-powered auto-focus is not the same as
                    an image generated entirely by a diffusion model.
                </p>
                <p class="text-warm-gray">
                    Our tiers respect that nuance. They let creators be honest about their process without being
                    penalised for using any tool at all. And they let consumers make informed choices based on what
                    matters to them.
                </p>
                <p class="text-warm-gray">
                    <strong>Transparency isn&rsquo;t about perfection &mdash; it&rsquo;s about honesty.</strong>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5 offset-lg-1">
                <div class="card card-cp">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="text-terracotta">The CraftPledge Promise</h4>
                        <p class="text-warm-gray mb-3">Every certified creator pledges to:</p>
                        <ul class="text-warm-gray">
                            <li class="mb-2">Be transparent about how their work is made</li>
                            <li class="mb-2">Accurately represent their tier level</li>
                            <li class="mb-2">Submit to verification processes</li>
                            <li class="mb-2">Update their certification if their process changes</li>
                            <li>Stand behind their claims with accountability</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Find the right tier for your work</h2>
        <p>Whether you use AI as a tool or work entirely by hand, there&rsquo;s a place for you in CraftPledge.</p>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ForCreators" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Take the Pledge</a>
    </div>
</section>
